The paper focuses on learning semantic representations of sentences using visual information, which is a common theme in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) research. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which includes research on NLP. The paper also uses deep neural networks, which is a common technique in machine learning (ML) research, particularly in the subfield of deep learning (DL), which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) tasks, such as image-caption retrieval, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper uses multimodal data, which involves both text and images, and therefore could also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision), which includes research on image and video processing.
